## The Equilibrium Problem

Traditional economics assumes equilibrium. Real markets do not.

### Key Insight
> "The map is not the territory."

Here is a list of reasons why:
1. Feedback loops
2. Agent adaptation
3. Network density

## Conclusion
We need better models.
